Best structure to follow

Based on the distinction example, this is the strongest order for your proposal:
	1.	Business context
	2.	Empathy map
	3.	User stories and acceptance criteria
	4.	Functional requirements
	5.	Non-functional requirements
	6.	Decomposition
	7.	KPIs
	8.	Description of proposed solution
	9.	Justification of how it meets client and user needs
	10.	Risk mitigation
	11.	Legal and regulatory requirements
	12.	Appendices with research notes

The biggest mistake to avoid

Do not just describe features. You need to keep linking everything back to:
	•	the client’s needs
	•	the users’ needs
	•	why your choice is sensible
	•	how it will be tested, designed, and built

That is what lifts it towards the top marks, and that is exactly what the distinction example does.  ￼

